### Question:
 Think of everyday situations that simulation could analyze. What aspects of the situation make the simulation
 approach specifically appropriate for analyzing the situation
(i.e., think about and explain why simulation would be specifically better than experimenting in the real world).
What aspects of sustainability can you incorporate into the simulation



### Answer:
A real-world local bank operational system will have the following variability, complexity, and interconnectedness.
    - Variability:
      + Customers: A random number of customers will come to the bank every day
      + Employees: The number of Employees who work for the bank
      + Desks: The number of desks available
      + Time: The time waiting for the Customer's turn
      + The process update time of the system

    - Complexity:
        + The number of desks available
        + The waiting time for each turn
        + The number of customers
        + The number of employees
        + The update process of the system

    - Interconnectedness:
        + If one employee is absent or the number of desks are not sufficient, the waiting time increase
        + If the update process slow down or crash out, then the waiting time will increase